256
00:14:37,798 --> 00:14:40,698
-Aosato Shuhei! -Aosato Shuhei!

257
00:14:40,698 --> 00:14:42,598
-Hey! -You...

258
00:14:42,598 --> 00:14:45,698
No way. Don't take them seriously.

259
00:14:45,698 --> 00:14:49,098
No one's going to make a culprit out of me

260
00:14:49,098 --> 00:14:51,198
using such a riddle like reason.

261
00:14:51,198 --> 00:14:52,898
But...

262
00:14:52,898 --> 00:14:56,298
It seems pretty logical to me.

263
00:14:57,398 --> 00:14:59,898
But, if I'm the culprit

264
00:14:59,898 --> 00:15:02,098
all she had to do was write my name as is, right?

265
00:15:02,098 --> 00:15:06,098
She probably thought that you'd erase it if she did.

266
00:15:06,098 --> 00:15:11,098
You know, when you come back here to confirm if she died.

267
00:15:11,098 --> 00:15:13,398
What're you talking about?

268
00:15:13,398 --> 00:15:16,698
Did you see me come here or what?

269
00:15:16,698 --> 00:15:18,698
No, we didn't.

270
00:15:18,698 --> 00:15:23,798
But, we know the other reason why you came here today, Mr. Aosato.

271
00:15:23,798 --> 00:15:24,898
What?

272
00:15:24,898 --> 00:15:27,698
To switch the regulator.

273
00:15:27,698 --> 00:15:32,398
You probably slashed the pipe of Hikari's regulator with a knife

274
00:15:32,398 --> 00:15:36,698
and after faking an air leak brought her here to Ikkaku Rock

275
00:15:36,698 --> 00:15:38,898
lied to her saying that you'd be coming back to get her

276
00:15:38,898 --> 00:15:40,898
and left her behind like you did, right?

277
00:15:41,898 --> 00:15:44,898
People don't come to Ikkaku Rock

278
00:15:44,898 --> 00:15:49,098
and since Hikari can't swim you figured she couldn't escape.

279
00:15:49,098 --> 00:15:52,598
In other words, you came to switch

280
00:15:52,598 --> 00:15:56,798
that slashed regulator with your own.

281
00:15:56,798 --> 00:15:58,598
If the slash is found later,

282
00:15:58,598 --> 00:16:00,598
the case would not be handled as an accident.

283
00:16:00,598 --> 00:16:03,498
If you close off the slash with a vinyl tape or something,

284
00:16:03,498 --> 00:16:06,198
you can make it back with that regulator.

285
00:16:06,198 --> 00:16:09,398
So, I'm asking if you guys saw me do that?

286
00:16:09,398 --> 00:16:11,298
The band-aid by your lip...

287
00:16:12,298 --> 00:16:15,698
You said that you busted a pimple

288
00:16:15,698 --> 00:16:17,598
while you were net surfing at an internet cafe

289
00:16:17,598 --> 00:16:20,598
with your head in your hands, right?

290
00:16:20,598 --> 00:16:23,798
Most of the mouse in internet cafes are for right-handed people.

291
00:16:23,798 --> 00:16:27,298
Which means that you were holding your head with your left hand

292
00:16:27,298 --> 00:16:31,798
so the busted pimple should naturally be below your left chin.

293
00:16:31,798 --> 00:16:34,198
But, judging from the position of the bandage...

294
00:16:34,198 --> 00:16:36,198
The Band-Aid is not under your left side, is it?

295
00:16:37,198 --> 00:16:39,098
It got smeared on, didn't it?

296
00:16:39,098 --> 00:16:41,998
When you went back to the boat to switch regulators

297
00:16:41,998 --> 00:16:44,498
with Hikari's and put it in your mouth?

298
00:16:44,498 --> 00:16:45,698
Oh, no...

299
00:16:47,498 --> 00:16:49,498
Hikari's lipstick.

300
00:16:51,398 --> 00:16:54,998
I see. When you got on board and wiped your mouth

301
00:16:54,998 --> 00:16:58,198
you realized for the first time that lipstick was smeared on you.

302
00:16:58,198 --> 00:17:00,698
So, you hid the lipstick that smeared under your right lip

303
00:17:00,698 --> 00:17:04,598
by using Band-Aid, right?

304
00:17:04,598 --> 00:17:07,298
Lipstick doesn't come off that easily

305
00:17:07,298 --> 00:17:10,198
just by wiping it off with your hand.

306
00:17:10,198 --> 00:17:12,898
But, she sure is a strange diver.

307
00:17:12,898 --> 00:17:14,698
I mean if she was a beginner I can see,

308
00:17:14,698 --> 00:17:16,598
but, she's been diving for some time,

309
00:17:16,598 --> 00:17:19,398
and yet why did she dive without removing her lipstick?

310
00:17:19,398 --> 00:17:20,998
She did so deliberately.

311
00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:23,598
When she first started diving,

312
00:17:23,598 --> 00:17:26,998
I mistakenly used her regulator and got lipstick smeared on me.

313
00:17:26,998 --> 00:17:29,098
She thought that was funny,

314
00:17:29,098 --> 00:17:33,498
so she continued to keep her lipstick on when diving.

315
00:17:34,698 --> 00:17:37,498
Well... thanks to that,

316
00:17:37,498 --> 00:17:41,698
we found out that Hikari left Yoshiro to die.

317
00:17:42,698 --> 00:17:44,298
Left him to die?

318
00:17:44,298 --> 00:17:48,398
Do you remember the accident 6 months ago?

319
00:17:48,398 --> 00:17:53,498
Yes, you mean when Hikari was taken by the current at the lake

320
00:17:53,498 --> 00:17:56,098
and Yoshiro went to save her.

321
00:17:56,098 --> 00:17:58,498
We somehow managed to find Hikari

322
00:17:58,498 --> 00:18:00,598
and pull her up to the boat but...

323
00:18:00,598 --> 00:18:04,898
Yoshiro was dead a while later.

324
00:18:04,898 --> 00:18:08,898
Hey, don't tell me that Yoshiro was near Hikari back then too?

325
00:18:09,898 --> 00:18:11,398
Yes, it's likely.

326
00:18:11,398 --> 00:18:14,598
But, that isn't what she said back then.

327
00:18:15,598 --> 00:18:19,298
I'm alone. Sorry and let me on board.

328
00:18:19,298 --> 00:18:21,498
It's so cold I'll freeze to death.

329
00:18:21,498 --> 00:18:23,898
So, we all thought...

330
00:18:23,898 --> 00:18:27,098
She didn't see Yoshiro.

331
00:18:27,098 --> 00:18:29,698
Of course, she saw him,

332
00:18:29,698 --> 00:18:33,298
because on the Yoshiro's rescue regulator that was found later.

333
00:18:33,298 --> 00:18:38,198
Hikari's lipstick was smeared all over it.

334
00:18:38,198 --> 00:18:40,098
When I pushed her for an answer,

335
00:18:40,098 --> 00:18:41,598
she said that she thought that Yoshiro

336
00:18:41,598 --> 00:18:44,598
had already swum back to land but...

337
00:18:44,598 --> 00:18:46,798
Isn't it natural to ask right away?

338
00:18:46,798 --> 00:18:48,698
About Yoshiro who came to rescue her

339
00:18:48,698 --> 00:18:52,298
and got caught in the current again, wondering if he's okay.

340
00:18:52,298 --> 00:18:55,198
All she was concerned about was getting back on land

341
00:18:55,198 --> 00:18:58,198
and jumping into a warm bed!

342
00:18:58,198 --> 00:19:02,598
She could care less if Yoshiro lived or died!

343
00:19:02,598 --> 00:19:09,398
That's why I left that woman behind at Ikkaku Rock here.

344
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:10,698
Well...

345
00:19:15,098 --> 00:19:18,098
You're all going to experience the same thing!

346
00:19:18,098 --> 00:19:20,698
Shuhei, don't be stupid!

347
00:19:22,498 --> 00:19:24,198
Don't worry.

348
00:19:24,198 --> 00:19:27,398
I'm just going to buy time until I get out of here.

349
00:19:27,398 --> 00:19:29,998
You guys are staying here for a while.

350
00:19:29,998 --> 00:19:31,698
Hey, officer!

351
00:19:31,698 --> 00:19:34,298
Tell your men on board the boat,

352
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:37,998
that you're returning on my cruiser while listening to my story,

353
00:19:37,998 --> 00:19:40,398
so to go on back without you.

354
00:19:40,398 --> 00:19:43,798
And when the police boat is out of sight...

355
00:19:43,798 --> 00:19:45,498
Fisherman!

356
00:19:45,498 --> 00:19:51,298
Cut the rope that is tied to the rock and let it go.

357
00:19:51,298 --> 00:19:53,698
When the fishing boat is out of sight,

358
00:19:53,698 --> 00:19:55,898
I'm taking this child

359
00:19:55,898 --> 00:19:58,898
and getting out of here with the cruiser!

360
00:19:58,898 --> 00:20:02,998
Darn. My watch type tranquilizer gun's on the boat.

361
00:20:02,998 --> 00:20:04,598
Although it's a bit dangerous

362
00:20:04,598 --> 00:20:07,498
I'll use my super kick shoe.

363
00:20:07,498 --> 00:20:10,598
I'm wearing boots.

364
00:20:10,598 --> 00:20:14,498
Hey, Ai, don't you have anything that may serve as a weapon?

365
00:20:14,498 --> 00:20:17,198
What makes you think I'd have something so convenient on me.

366
00:20:23,698 --> 00:20:26,498
0.12 percent...

367
00:20:26,498 --> 00:20:27,898
What?

368
00:20:27,898 --> 00:20:31,898
That's the rate that a culprit makes a safe escape.

369
00:20:31,898 --> 00:20:34,198
It's one in a thousand people.

370
00:20:34,198 --> 00:20:38,898
But, those few who have received the blessing of the devil

371
00:20:38,898 --> 00:20:41,998
and fled will eventually tire from hiding their true identities,

372
00:20:41,998 --> 00:20:44,798
living in fear and continue living on.

373
00:20:44,798 --> 00:20:46,498
Putting aside those who have confessed

374
00:20:46,498 --> 00:20:49,198
to their crime or committed suicide,

375
00:20:49,198 --> 00:20:52,198
the success rated is virtually...

376
00:20:52,198 --> 00:20:54,298
nil.

377
00:20:55,298 --> 00:20:57,198
Will you be able to endure being all alone

378
00:20:57,198 --> 00:21:01,698
as well as the pressure of all that is to come?

379
00:21:02,698 --> 00:21:03,998
Shut up!

380
00:21:16,998 --> 00:21:20,298
Okay, you're fine now.

381
00:21:20,298 --> 00:21:21,398
Thank you.

382
00:21:26,198 --> 00:21:30,498
Well, then, shall we have you flee all the way to the station?

383
00:21:30,498 --> 00:21:32,398
Yes, sir.

384
00:21:35,698 --> 00:21:37,898
You're sure strong!

385
00:21:37,898 --> 00:21:39,698
Really awesome!

386
00:21:39,698 --> 00:21:40,998
Not really...

387
00:21:40,998 --> 00:21:43,598
Thank you, Subaru.

388
00:21:43,598 --> 00:21:49,198
Is what you said about 0.12 percent really true?

389
00:21:49,198 --> 00:21:51,798
Of course, it's a lie.

390
00:21:53,598 --> 00:21:55,298
I thought I had no choice

391
00:21:55,298 --> 00:21:58,198
but to provoke him if I wanted him to divert

392
00:21:58,198 --> 00:22:00,598
the knife away from her.

393
00:22:00,598 --> 00:22:02,498
You're really something after all.

394
00:23:52,498 --> 00:23:55,398
Just as I thought. He's...

395
00:24:01,498 --> 00:24:03,198
She has been choked to death.

396
00:24:03,198 --> 00:24:04,498
Manual strangulation.

397
00:24:04,498 --> 00:24:07,098
Excuse me. There are green stains

398
00:24:07,098 --> 00:24:10,198
on both shoulders of Ms. Yukiko.

399
00:24:10,198 --> 00:24:13,998
Yukiko took the stairs all the way down to B1.

400
00:24:13,998 --> 00:24:16,598
Why didn't she use the elevator?

401
00:24:16,598 --> 00:24:19,998
The one who killed Yukiko...

402
00:24:19,998 --> 00:24:21,498
is among them.

